---
abstract: RPackUtils: R package dependencies manager and Bioconductor/CRAN mirroring tool
---
full_description:

The installation and maintenance of R packages from public
repositories, such as the Comprehensive R Archive Network (CRAN) or
Bioconductor, is a process made cumbersome by the need to manage
package dependencies. Typically, this forces users to download the
versions of the package that are currently available and potentially
experience a trial-and-error cycle of installing and updating all
dependencies. The reproducibility of an R installation, and therefore
of the R code itself, is not guaranteed by the use of standard,
out-of-the-box tools.

RPackUtils is an R package dependencies manager developed in Python
with reproducibility in mind. RPackUtils can manage several public and
private repositories (e.g., Artifactory), any existing R environment,
or any local file system folder internally as well as install packages
from all of them and mirror the main public repositories, CRAN and
Bioconductor, to a specific snapshot in time or release.
